The paper discusses graph analytics SQL queries and their efficient execution using an in-memory analytics engine. This topic falls under the database (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS) categories. The use of aggregation functions and measure attributes suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the use of compression methods and query optimization techniques may also relate to machine learning (cs.LG).
